This is the Private Health Insurance Tax Claim Code from the immediate prior year reported by an individual taxpayer.
The 'PHI - Tax Claim Code' will be prefilled when the tax claim code from the immediate prior year is the same code for all Private Health Insurance policies reported in the previous year for a given client (eg. client has reported multiple tax claim code A in the previous year). The 'PHI - Tax Claim Code' will not be prefilled where the spouse status has changed from the immediate prior year or where the individual was covered as a dependant child in the immediate prior year and will be aged over 25 on 30th June of the current year.
